âŒ What NEVER Happens During Failure

When governance fails, the system cannot:

Rewrite or amend past records

Partially update the ledger

â€œFix upâ€ results silently

Auto-retry with modified parameters

Override validation by role or authority

These code paths do not exist.

ğŸ“¦ Where Failed Emissions Go: The Mutable Shell

Rejected emissions are preserved, not erased.

Properties of the mutable shell:

Separate storage from the fossil ledger

No hash chaining

No authority

Re-evaluatable later

Never treated as truth

This allows experimentation without contaminating governance.

ğŸ§  Why This Is Safe Failure

Because:

Failure is forward-only

Authority is append-only

Validation is stateful and external

Power is structurally constrained

Failure does not weaken governance.
It demonstrates its boundaries.

